        <page n="05" image="pa.fr.fr.1859.03.02.05">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>A Magnificent Concert</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The article is a play on the coming of spring as a magnificent concert
                    itself, but does note Chambersburg's reputation for good music, the existence of
                    "fifty or sixty Pianos in town, two or three excellent string Bands, one Brass
                    Band, which cannot be excelled, and vocal musicians without number."</summary>
                <note/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>none</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"Daniel S. Funk, convicted of murder in the second degree at the last term
                    of our Court for the killing of John osborn, and sentenced to be imprisoned for
                    the period of five years and six months in the Eastern Penitentiary, was
                    conveyed thither, by the Sheriff, on Thursday week."</excerpt>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Notes Mr. Funk's transportation to prison.</summary>
                <note/>
            </div>
